Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setOutboundReport(25.10)                              setOutboundReport(25.10)

Name
       setOutboundReport  -  Controls  what extrapolation information is to be
       saved in the log file(s)

Syntax
       setOutboundReport

       [-help]

       -delay {early | late | both}

       [-filename_prefix <string>]

       [-report_constant_nets {true | false}]

       [-type {lower | upper | both}]

       Controls what extrapolation information is  to  be  saved  in  the  log
       file(s). The slew extrapolation information can be stored into separate
       files.

       When this command is not specified, slew extrapolation will be reported
       for  both  minimum and maximum analysis, if outbound reporting has been
       enabled by specifying the setDelayCalMode -reportOutBound true command.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage

       -delay {early | late | both}
              Control whether extrapolation information is to be shown for min
              or max (or both) analyses.

              Default: both

       -filename_prefix <string>
              Specify the prefix to be used  in  the  name(s)  of  the  report
              file(s).

              Default: design-name

       -report_constant_nets {true | false}
              Controls  whether  extrapolation  information is to be shown for
              constant nets or not.

       -type {lower | upper | both}
              Controls whether extrapolation information is to  be  shown  for
              lower or upper (or both) outbound slews.

Examples
       The following command will will dump slew extrapolation information for
       maximum   analysis   into   the   myreport.dc.outbound.slew.late.<view-
       name>.txt file:

       setOutboundReport -delay late -filename_prefix myreport

